headline.main: AIR BLOWS TRADED OVER NORTH AFRICA; German Attacks on Bone Are Beaten Off as Allies Bomb Tunis Port, Rail Yards

lead_paragraph: ALLIED HEADQUARTERS IN NORTH AFRICA, Jan. 2 -- Three times yesterday the German air force attempted to attack the vital harbor at Bone, Algeria, near the Tunisian frontier. The first time the Royal Air Force succeeded in blocking the raiders and the other two attacks were turned back before getting near their objective.
abstract: Allies bomb Tunis port and rr yards
